<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-276] Add commands leading to setattr to the doc/protocol document</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-276</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The shell commands &apos;chmod&apos;, &apos;chown&apos;, &apos;chgrp&apos; and &apos;touch&apos; (of an existing file) issue POSIX system&lt;br/&gt;
calls &apos;chmod()&apos;, &apos;chown()&apos;, &apos;chown()&apos;, and &apos;stat()&apos;, respectively; each of which results in a call to &apos;ll_setattr()&apos; in lustre/llite/llite_lib.c.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Document the messages exchanged to carry out these operations as well as any state change they can cause.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
